This paper is primarily focused on natural language processing tasks, specifically named entity recognition, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning and active learning, which are both popular topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The model architecture described in the paper involves convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and long short term memory (LSTM) networks, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and neural engineering (cs.NE).
